{
  "stem": "17761.3",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 177.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Everybody had the right to take with him a parcel of five kilograms.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "That's about 10, 12 pounds or something like this.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I remember that this very-- this morning, that was the last time that we made our prayer in our temple.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I led the prayer.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I did it in such a speed that I don't think that it would ever be able to do that-- this in such a speed.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "We all profaned Shabbat.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "We had no choice.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And we prepared what we have to prepare, because we had to go to the train station on Shabbat.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I'll come to that.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And my mother made up such little bags for everybody.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Every child had to carry its own bag.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And naturally, I had also my bag.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And suddenly came in the-- Dr.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Druchman was his name, the gabbai, or the president, of our synagogue with a little Sefer Torah.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "This Sefer Torah has been written about 150 years ago counting from today at the inauguration of this temple by one of his ancestors, who was the founder and the first gabbai of this temple.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And he said to my-- to my father in Yiddish, Herr Leibisch, I would like to save at least once Sefer Torah from our synagogue.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I don't know what will happen.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I know that if you will take it, it will be saved.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So my father turned to me.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "He said to me, [NON-ENGLISH]-- he used to use this diminutive-- [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "This will be your bag.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I took all the things that my mother gave me, took them out from the bag and put in this little Sefer Torah, And with that, we went to the concentration-- to the-- may I just-- I-- we saw-- with that, we were deported.",
      "word_count": 45
    }
  ],
